id":"abcfee1a-8124-4ed8-8cfb-4826a572dcdd","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":12,"value":"93f44085-a759-46d1-924c-439e1f3a431e","text":"Settignan","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false}],"blockProperties":[{"id":"7cf52ecf-4510-4648-a74d-c638573bd971","type":"block/alignment/right","metadata":{},"isDeleted":false}],"children":[],"metadata":{},"relation":{}},{"id":"b371dde4-288d-44ee-9a40-b928c7e35f66","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"\r","standoffProperties":[],"blockProperties":[],"children":[],"metadata":{},"relation":{}},{"id":"4f04a114-c262-40f5-9944-cf5853e3bd2c","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Lodovico, — I shall only reply to such portions of your letter as seem to call for an answer: as for the remainder, I laugh at it. You tell me that you could not obtain your money from the Monte because I have had it registered in my name. This is not true, and I must reply sufficiently to convince you that you have been deceived by the person in whom you trusted, who has, perhaps, withdrawn the money for his own use, telling you this story in order to shield himself. I did not have the money registered in my name in the Monte, nor could I have done so had I desired: but it is true that the notary said to me, in the hearing of Raffaello da Gagliano: — \"I do not wish thy brothers to enter into a contract with the Monte, which, after the death of your father, would leave thee with no control over the money.\" He then took me to the Monte, where I had to spend fifteen grossoni, and added a provision to the contract to the effect that nobody should be entitled to touch the money as long as you lived. Under this contract, as you already know, you are made the beneficiary for life.\r","standoffProperties":[{"id":"4445e6aa-2afd-4be2-9f42-6014375fd4d6","type":"codex/meta-relation-reference","start":0,"end":7,"value":"84e60eef-fac4-49c1-b452-b530301bfcd7","text":"Lodovic","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false},{"id":"8edf7632-7b91-41e1-83